DOUBLE YUM! I had a very ripe pineapple that needed to be used, and this recipe sounded like it would fit the bill. Made it for my dinner at my In-Laws tonight - and it was a huge hit. Some of the people don't drink, so for those who wished, I just poured some Jamaican Rum on the plate before putting the cake piece on, and it soaked it up prior to making it to the table. Put a scoop of Vanilla Bean ice cream on the side, and Voila! I think it's key in a cake like this to have a VERY SWEET and RIPE pineapple - since it's the star flavor you will get. I found the cake moist, and yet held firm and was able to soak in some rum still. Perfectly balanced, upgraded comfort food.

