Rating: 4
My sweetie requested this cake for his birthday. I'd never even seen pineapple upside down cake before but this recipe had rave reviews. They were right! Everyone loved this cake. Most people had two pieces! My changes: I doubled the recipe and baked in a 12" round cast iron skillet. Cut pineapple into lengthwise 1/4" slices, arranged like a "sun" around a 12" cast iron skillet. For double recipe: Added 1/2 cup rum, 1 tsp cinnamon, used all dark brown sugar (no white) and substituted yogurt for buttermilk. Had to cook about 1 hour (maybe due to high altitude, yogurt, and/or rum). Wait for cast-iron skillet to cool or the sugar will run out and not soak into the cake.

